commit_list.message:
Fix attribute inheritance when subclassing

This patch enables proper inheritance

  class A < Couchbase::Model
    attribute :one
  end

  class B < A
    attribute :two
  end

  A.attributes              #=> {:one => nil}
  B.attributes              #=> {:one => nil, :two => nil}

  B.attributes.object_id != A.attributes.object_id  #=> true

Reset Couchbase#thread_storage when a Kernel#fork is detected
